A small and simple lex/yacc based calculator that can handle floats.

Supports basic arithmetic and logic functions, with PEMDAS precedence rules.
Supports decimal, octal, hex and binary numbers (prefix with "0", "0x" and "0b", respectively)
Supports hexadecimal real numbers
Supports functions, using "&" as a function prefix:
	 &sin(), &cos(), &sqrt(), &tan(), &atan(), &log(), &ln(), &log2()
Supports variables, using ":=" for assignment, and with support for persistent variable values
"e" and "pi" are available as constants.
Supports setting the decimal precision f√∂r output, using the pseudo-function "#": #(2, 1+1)


Please keep in mind that this code is incredibly old.